\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
Subpart (g)
\series default
 Remember in the signaling models from class and section, we only had two
 possible messages that could be sent by the Sender.
 This resulted in two information sets for the Receiver.
 By the same logic, since there are an infinite number of prices (messages),
 we have an infinite number of information sets for which we must set the
 regulator's level of action:
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula \[
S_{Regulator}\equiv\left\{ I(p)\in[0,1]:p\in P\right\} ,\]

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $P$
\end_inset

 is the set of all possible equilibrium prices.
 This won't be that big of a problem.
 
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\end_layout

